fields.description:
When trying to remove/add a new storage controller into an existing availability zone, the following error is given in {{cloud-debug.log}} on the SC node:
{noformat}
Tue Jan 10 14:37:56 2017 ERROR [EmpyreanService:New I/O worker #282] java.util.concurrent.ExecutionException: java.lang.RuntimeException: com.eucalyptus.util.fsm.ExistingTransitionException: Transition request state=LOADED rejected because of an ongoing transition: State:name=arn:euca:eucalyptus:zone-a:storage:sc-192.168.1.11/:state=INITIALIZED:mark=true:transition=TRANSITION arn:euca:eucalyptus:zone-a:storage:sc-192.168.1.11/ #618 LOAD ActiveTransition name=LOAD from=INITIALIZED/false to=LOADED/false error=BROKEN action=LOAD id=618 startTime=Tue Jan 10 14:35:46 PST 2017
java.util.concurrent.ExecutionException: java.lang.RuntimeException: com.eucalyptus.util.fsm.ExistingTransitionException: Transition request state=LOADED rejected because of an ongoing transition: State:name=arn:euca:eucalyptus:zone-a:storage:sc-192.168.1.11/:state=INITIALIZED:mark=true:transition=TRANSITION arn:euca:eucalyptus:zone-a:storage:sc-192.168.1.11/ #618 LOAD ActiveTransition name=LOAD from=INITIALIZED/false to=LOADED/false error=BROKEN action=LOAD id=618 startTime=Tue Jan 10 14:35:46 PST 2017
{noformat}

To reproduce the problem:
# Remove existing SC from the CLC
{noformat}euserv-deregister-service sc-192.168.1.10{noformat}
# Register new SC node to CLC
{noformat}
clcadmin-copy-keys -z zone-a 192.168.1.11
euserv-register-service -t storage -h 192.168.1.11 -z zone-a sc-192.168.1.11
{noformat}
# Configure storage (in this case for ceph)
{noformat}
euctl zone-a.storage.blockstoragemanager=ceph-rbd
{noformat}

comments.body:
Found the problem...SELINUX!  It seems the service cannot be initialized due to the fact it gets a socket connection failure when trying to initialize ldap.
{noformat}
2017-01-10 18:23:00 ERROR | javax.naming.CommunicationException: ldap1.mydomain.com:389 [Root exception is java.net.SocketException: Permission denied (connect failed)]
javax.naming.CommunicationException: ldap1.devlnk.net:389 [Root exception is java.net.SocketException: Permission denied (connect failed)]
{noformat}

When looking at the audit log you can see there are failures for eucalyptus
{noformat}
tail -1000 audit.log | audit2allow

#============= eucalyptus_cloud_t ==============

#!!!! This avc can be allowed using the boolean 'eucalyptus_storage_controller'
allow eucalyptus_cloud_t cyphesis_port_t:tcp_socket name_connect;

#!!!! This avc can be allowed using the boolean 'eucalyptus_storage_controller'
allow eucalyptus_cloud_t eucalyptus_tmp_t:file execute;
allow eucalyptus_cloud_t ldap_port_t:tcp_socket name_connect;
{noformat}

I verified this was the case by setting SELinux to 'permissive' and was able to start up the SC node and register it with the CLC.

[~gholms], I just discovered that an issue we have had with LDAP this past week was due to the fact that simply setting {{eucalyptus_cloud_t}} to permissive was not enough. We still were getting the following AVC denied message:
{noformat}
type=AVC msg=audit(1486462969.444:1776): avc:  denied  { name_connect } for  pid=23710 comm="eucalyptus-clou" dest=389 scontext=system_u:system_r:eucalyptus_cloud_t:s0 tcontext=system_u:object_r:ldap_port_t:s0 tclass=tcp_socket
type=SYSCALL msg=audit(1486462969.444:1776): arch=c000003e syscall=42 success=yes exit=0 a0=309 a1=7f6093cba8a0 a2=10 a3=730a items=0 ppid=998 pid=23710 auid=4294967295 uid=995 gid=993 euid=995 suid=995 fsuid=995 egid=993 sgid=993 fsgid=993 tty=(none) ses=4294967295 comm="eucalyptus-clou" exe="/usr/sbin/eucalyptus-cloud" subj=system_u:system_r:eucalyptus_cloud_t:s0 key=(null)
{noformat}

As a temporary workaround (which I assume is in the updated module with 4.4) I created a single policy to allow ldap connections
{noformat}
cat << EOF > euca13102.te
module euca13102 0.0.1;

require {
        type eucalyptus_cloud_t;
        type ldap_port_t;
        class tcp_socket name_connect;
}

#============= eucalyptus_cloud_t ==============
allow eucalyptus_cloud_t ldap_port_t:tcp_socket name_connect;
EOF

make -f /usr/share/selinux/devel/Makefile
semodule -i euca13102.pp
{noformat}

When running {{audit2allow}} it properly now reports the avc is allowed in the current policy
{noformat}
cat /var/log/audit/audit.log | audit2allow
#============= eucalyptus_cloud_t ==============

#!!!! This avc is allowed in the current policy
allow eucalyptus_cloud_t ldap_port_t:tcp_socket name_connect;
{noformat}
